# CI/CD Rules

## Local Development
- Use `docker-compose.yml` for local multi-service setup (db, redis, etc.)
- Backend: `uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000`
- Frontend: `npm run dev` (Next.js dev server, port 3000)
- One command to start everything: `make dev` or `docker compose up`

## Docker
- Each service has its own Dockerfile
- Use multi-stage builds (builder → runner) to minimize image size
- Never copy `.env` or secrets into Docker images
- Pin base image versions (`python:3.12-slim`, not `python:latest`)

## GitHub Actions CI Pipeline
```yaml
# Suggested .github/workflows/ci.yml structure:
# on: [push, pull_request]
# jobs:
#   backend-lint:    ruff check backend/
#   backend-test:    pytest backend/tests/
#   frontend-lint:   npm run lint (in frontend/)
#   frontend-test:   npm run test (in frontend/)
#   typecheck:       npm run typecheck (in frontend/)
```

## Deployment Checklist
- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] No linter errors
- [ ] Environment variables documented
- [ ] Database migrations tested
- [ ] OpenAPI types synced (frontend matches backend)
- [ ] Docker images build successfully

## Environment Variables
- All config via env vars, never hardcode
- `.env.example` in repo root with all required vars (values empty or placeholder)
- Actual `.env` in `.gitignore`

## Database Migrations
- Use Alembic (Python) for schema migrations
- Always test migration up AND down (rollback)
- Never edit a migration that's already been applied to production
